<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="393" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3111: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-26T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 26, 1919,
                                        6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your May 23, 4 p.m., Tientsin affair.</p>
                        <p>Department approves and trusts you will be able to obtain a definite
                            reply before leaving for Siberia.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>